[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1338},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F":1317,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2025\u002F12\u002F05\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002F":1326},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20251205\u002F3653220664\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1301,"date":1302,"description":1303,"extension":1304,"lang":1305,"meta":1306,"navigation":137,"path":1307,"readingMinutes":1308,"seo":1309,"standalone":1310,"stem":1311,"tags":1312,"tldr":1314,"updated":1302,"url":1315,"__hash__":1316},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions.md","What Are JavaScript Generator Functions (function*)? The Function You Can Pause and Resume","1001496694",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1295},"minimark",[11,19,24,31,35,46,49,203,206,210,213,216,273,279,282,285,334,344,390,406,422,525,534,543,663,674,693,700,929,932,1121,1125,1136,1146,1155,1161,1282,1285,1291],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"What Are JavaScript Generator Functions (function*)?","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fjavascript\u002Fjavascript-generator-functions\u002FGemini_Generated_Image_x1sqeux1sqeux1sq.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26,30],{},[27,28,29],"code",{},"function*"," is one of those bits of syntax hardly anyone reaches for, but it's honestly pretty powerful. It lets you define a special kind of function called a \"generator function,\" so in this post I want to walk through what generator functions are and what you'd actually use them for.",[20,32,34],{"id":33},"so-whats-a-generator-function","So what's a generator function?",[12,36,37,38,41,42,45],{},"Basically, a generator function is a function you can \"pause\" and \"resume.\" How do you make one? It's simple — when you declare the function, you just add a star ",[27,39,40],{},"*"," right after the ",[27,43,44],{},"function"," keyword.",[12,47,48],{},"Here are a couple of ways to define a generator function:",[50,51,56],"pre",{"className":52,"code":53,"language":54,"meta":55,"style":55},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u002F\u002F Function statement - Generator Function\nfunction* myGenerator() {\n  console.log(\"Hello\");\n  yield; \u002F\u002F pause point\n  console.log(\"World\");\n}\n\n\u002F\u002F Function expression - Generator Function\nconst myGenerator = function* () {\n  console.log(\"Hello\");\n  yield; \u002F\u002F pause point\n  console.log(\"World\");\n};\n","js","",[27,57,58,67,81,100,112,126,132,139,145,162,175,184,197],{"__ignoreMap":55},[59,60,63],"span",{"class":61,"line":62},"line",1,[59,64,66],{"class":65},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F Function statement - Generator Function\n",[59,68,70,73,77],{"class":61,"line":69},2,[59,71,29],{"class":72},"sWyjQ",[59,74,76],{"class":75},"sj_SG"," myGenerator",[59,78,80],{"class":79},"sMAXC","() {\n",[59,82,84,87,90,93,97],{"class":61,"line":83},3,[59,85,86],{"class":79},"  console.",[59,88,89],{"class":75},"log",[59,91,92],{"class":79},"(",[59,94,96],{"class":95},"sTRMh","\"Hello\"",[59,98,99],{"class":79},");\n",[59,101,103,106,109],{"class":61,"line":102},4,[59,104,105],{"class":72},"  yield",[59,107,108],{"class":79},"; ",[59,110,111],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F pause point\n",[59,113,115,117,119,121,124],{"class":61,"line":114},5,[59,116,86],{"class":79},[59,118,89],{"class":75},[59,120,92],{"class":79},[59,122,123],{"class":95},"\"World\"",[59,125,99],{"class":79},[59,127,129],{"class":61,"line":128},6,[59,130,131],{"class":79},"}\n",[59,133,135],{"class":61,"line":134},7,[59,136,138],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":137},true,"\n",[59,140,142],{"class":61,"line":141},8,[59,143,144],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F Function expression - Generator Function\n",[59,146,148,151,153,156,159],{"class":61,"line":147},9,[59,149,150],{"class":72},"const",[59,152,76],{"class":75},[59,154,155],{"class":72}," =",[59,157,158],{"class":72}," function*",[59,160,161],{"class":79}," () {\n",[59,163,165,167,169,171,173],{"class":61,"line":164},10,[59,166,86],{"class":79},[59,168,89],{"class":75},[59,170,92],{"class":79},[59,172,96],{"class":95},[59,174,99],{"class":79},[59,176,178,180,182],{"class":61,"line":177},11,[59,179,105],{"class":72},[59,181,108],{"class":79},[59,183,111],{"class":65},[59,185,187,189,191,193,195],{"class":61,"line":186},12,[59,188,86],{"class":79},[59,190,89],{"class":75},[59,192,92],{"class":79},[59,194,123],{"class":95},[59,196,99],{"class":79},[59,198,200],{"class":61,"line":199},13,[59,201,202],{"class":79},"};\n",[12,204,205],{},"One thing to watch out for: generator functions don't support arrow function syntax directly. So you can only use a traditional function declaration or a function expression to define one.",[20,207,209],{"id":208},"why-would-you-need-generator-functions","Why would you need generator functions?",[12,211,212],{},"Let's look at a few situations where you'd actually reach for a generator function.",[12,214,215],{},"Normally when you build a function:",[50,217,219],{"className":52,"code":218,"language":54,"meta":55,"style":55},"function myFunction() {\n  console.log(\"Hello\");\n  console.log(\"World\");\n}\n\nmyFunction(); \u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello\" and \"World\"\n",[27,220,221,230,242,254,258,262],{"__ignoreMap":55},[59,222,223,225,228],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,224,44],{"class":72},[59,226,227],{"class":75}," myFunction",[59,229,80],{"class":79},[59,231,232,234,236,238,240],{"class":61,"line":69},[59,233,86],{"class":79},[59,235,89],{"class":75},[59,237,92],{"class":79},[59,239,96],{"class":95},[59,241,99],{"class":79},[59,243,244,246,248,250,252],{"class":61,"line":83},[59,245,86],{"class":79},[59,247,89],{"class":75},[59,249,92],{"class":79},[59,251,123],{"class":95},[59,253,99],{"class":79},[59,255,256],{"class":61,"line":102},[59,257,131],{"class":79},[59,259,260],{"class":61,"line":114},[59,261,138],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":137},[59,263,264,267,270],{"class":61,"line":128},[59,265,266],{"class":75},"myFunction",[59,268,269],{"class":79},"(); ",[59,271,272],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello\" and \"World\"\n",[12,274,275,276,278],{},"You can see that once you call ",[27,277,266],{},", the function runs from start to finish — there's no pausing partway through.",[12,280,281],{},"But sometimes what you really need is for the function to pause partway through and wait for the next call, depending on how some condition changes. That's exactly where generator functions come in.",[12,283,284],{},"And the usage is super simple:",[50,286,288],{"className":52,"code":287,"language":54,"meta":55,"style":55},"function* myGenerator() {\n  console.log(\"Hello\");\n  yield; \u002F\u002F pause point\n  console.log(\"World\");\n}\n",[27,289,290,298,310,318,330],{"__ignoreMap":55},[59,291,292,294,296],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,293,29],{"class":72},[59,295,76],{"class":75},[59,297,80],{"class":79},[59,299,300,302,304,306,308],{"class":61,"line":69},[59,301,86],{"class":79},[59,303,89],{"class":75},[59,305,92],{"class":79},[59,307,96],{"class":95},[59,309,99],{"class":79},[59,311,312,314,316],{"class":61,"line":83},[59,313,105],{"class":72},[59,315,108],{"class":79},[59,317,111],{"class":65},[59,319,320,322,324,326,328],{"class":61,"line":102},[59,321,86],{"class":79},[59,323,89],{"class":75},[59,325,92],{"class":79},[59,327,123],{"class":95},[59,329,99],{"class":79},[59,331,332],{"class":61,"line":114},[59,333,131],{"class":79},[12,335,336,337,340,341,343],{},"You just drop a ",[27,338,339],{},"yield"," keyword wherever you want to pause. When the function hits ",[27,342,339],{},", it pauses and waits for the next call.",[50,345,347],{"className":52,"code":346,"language":54,"meta":55,"style":55},"const gen = myGenerator(); \u002F\u002F create the generator object\ngen.next(); \u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello\"\ngen.next(); \u002F\u002F outputs \"World\"\n",[27,348,349,366,379],{"__ignoreMap":55},[59,350,351,353,357,359,361,363],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,352,150],{"class":72},[59,354,356],{"class":355},"sCcAr"," gen",[59,358,155],{"class":72},[59,360,76],{"class":75},[59,362,269],{"class":79},[59,364,365],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F create the generator object\n",[59,367,368,371,374,376],{"class":61,"line":69},[59,369,370],{"class":79},"gen.",[59,372,373],{"class":75},"next",[59,375,269],{"class":79},[59,377,378],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello\"\n",[59,380,381,383,385,387],{"class":61,"line":83},[59,382,370],{"class":79},[59,384,373],{"class":75},[59,386,269],{"class":79},[59,388,389],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F outputs \"World\"\n",[12,391,392,393,396,397,399,400,402,403,405],{},"Notice that ",[27,394,395],{},"gen"," doesn't run right away like a normal function would. Instead it returns a generator object, and that object has a ",[27,398,373],{}," method. Every time you call ",[27,401,373],{},", the function picks up from where it last paused and keeps going until it hits the next ",[27,404,339],{}," or the function ends.",[12,407,408,409,411,412,415,416,418,419,421],{},"On top of that, ",[27,410,339],{}," can hand back a value — like ",[27,413,414],{},"yield value"," — so when you call ",[27,417,373],{}," you can grab that value. So if you're the kind of dev who likes writing pure functions, you can get a similar effect through ",[27,420,339],{},".",[50,423,425],{"className":52,"code":424,"language":54,"meta":55,"style":55},"function* myGenerator(name) {\n  yield `Hello, ${name}`;\n  yield `${name}, what do you plan to get done today?`;\n}\nconst gen = myGenerator(\"Ming\");\nconsole.log(gen.next().value); \u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello, Ming\"\nconsole.log(gen.next().value); \u002F\u002F outputs \"Ming, what do you plan to get done today?\"\n",[27,426,427,442,457,471,475,492,510],{"__ignoreMap":55},[59,428,429,431,433,435,439],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,430,29],{"class":72},[59,432,76],{"class":75},[59,434,92],{"class":79},[59,436,438],{"class":437},"s_sBn","name",[59,440,441],{"class":79},") {\n",[59,443,444,446,449,451,454],{"class":61,"line":69},[59,445,105],{"class":72},[59,447,448],{"class":95}," `Hello, ${",[59,450,438],{"class":79},[59,452,453],{"class":95},"}`",[59,455,456],{"class":79},";\n",[59,458,459,461,464,466,469],{"class":61,"line":83},[59,460,105],{"class":72},[59,462,463],{"class":95}," `${",[59,465,438],{"class":79},[59,467,468],{"class":95},"}, what do you plan to get done today?`",[59,470,456],{"class":79},[59,472,473],{"class":61,"line":102},[59,474,131],{"class":79},[59,476,477,479,481,483,485,487,490],{"class":61,"line":114},[59,478,150],{"class":72},[59,480,356],{"class":355},[59,482,155],{"class":72},[59,484,76],{"class":75},[59,486,92],{"class":79},[59,488,489],{"class":95},"\"Ming\"",[59,491,99],{"class":79},[59,493,494,497,499,502,504,507],{"class":61,"line":128},[59,495,496],{"class":79},"console.",[59,498,89],{"class":75},[59,500,501],{"class":79},"(gen.",[59,503,373],{"class":75},[59,505,506],{"class":79},"().value); ",[59,508,509],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello, Ming\"\n",[59,511,512,514,516,518,520,522],{"class":61,"line":134},[59,513,496],{"class":79},[59,515,89],{"class":75},[59,517,501],{"class":79},[59,519,373],{"class":75},[59,521,506],{"class":79},[59,523,524],{"class":65},"\u002F\u002F outputs \"Ming, what do you plan to get done today?\"\n",[12,526,527,528,530,531,533],{},"Pretty fun, right? You can call ",[27,529,373],{}," whenever you want to pull the next ",[27,532,339],{}," value, which makes the function's execution way more flexible.",[12,535,536,537,539,540,542],{},"There's another thing: ",[27,538,373],{}," can also take an argument, and that argument becomes the return value of the previous ",[27,541,339],{}," expression. This lets the function decide its next move based on a value passed in from outside each time it resumes.",[50,544,546],{"className":52,"code":545,"language":54,"meta":55,"style":55},"function* myGenerator(name) {\n  const task = yield `Hello, ${name}`;\n  console.log(task);\n  yield `${name}, what do you plan to get done today? ${task}`;\n}\nconst gen = myGenerator(\"Ming\");\nconsole.log(gen.next().value); \u002F\u002F outputs \"Hello, Ming\"\nconsole.log(gen.next(\"write some code\").value); \u002F\u002F outputs \"Ming, what do you plan to get done today? write some code\"\n",[27,547,548,560,581,590,608,612,628,642],{"__ignoreMap":55},[59,549,550,552,554,556,558],{"class":61,"line":62},[59,551,29],{"class":72},[59,553,76],{"class":75},[59,555,92],{"class":79},[59,557,438],{"class":437},[59,559,441],{"class":79},[59,561,562,565,568,570,573,575,577,579],{"class":61,"line":69},[59,563,564],{"class":72},"  const",[59,566,567],{"class":355}," task",[59,569,155],{"class":72},[59,571,572],{"class":72}," yield",[59,574,448],{"class":95},[59,576,438],{"class":79},[59,578,453],{"class":95},[59,580,456],{"class":79},[59,582,583,585,587],{"class":61,"line":83},[59,584,86],{"class":79},[59,586,89],{"class":75},[59,588,589],{"class":79},"(task);\n",[59,591,592,594,596,598,601,604,606],{"class":61,"line":102},[59,593,105],{"class":72},[59,595,463],{"class":95},[59,597,438],{"class":79},[59,599,600],{"class":95},"}, what do you plan to get done today? ${",[59,602,603],{"class":79},"task",[59,605,453],{"class":95},[59,607,456],{"class":79},[59,609,610],{"class":61,"line":114},[59,611,131],{"class":79},[59,613,614,616,618,620,622,624,626],{"class":61,"line":128},[59,615,150],{"class":72},[59,617,356],{"class":355},[59,619,155],{"class":72},[59,621,76],{"class":75},[59,623,92],{"class":79},[59,625,489],{"class":95},[59,627,99],{"class":79},[59,629,630,632,634,636,638,640],{"class":61,"line":134},[59,631,496],{"class"